{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 08:31:31.509491", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary\\n- Overall fabric control plane (EBGP across leaves, spines, super-spine) is healthy and converged.\\n- The only identified anomaly is endpoint pc_0_1 being down (container not running), which makes 10.0.1.2 unreachable. The fabric correctly forwards to the leaf gateway 10.0.1.1 but cannot reach the host behind it.\\n\\nControl Plane Assessment (BGP)\\n- All EBGP sessions are established across the fabric:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200) peers up with both spines (172.16.0.4, 172.16.0.8), receiving prefixes (State/PfxRcd = 1 from each).\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201) peers up with both spines (172.16.0.6, 172.16.0.10), receiving prefixes (State/PfxRcd = 1 from each).\\n  - spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100) peers up with super-spine and both leaves (3 peers total).\\n  - spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101) peers up with super-spine and both leaves (3 peers total).\\n  - super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000) peers up with both spines (2 peers total).\\n- Route tables are consistent:\\n  - Leaves have their directly connected /24 (10.0.0.0/24 or 10.0.1.0/24) and learn the remote /24 via one of the spines:\\n    - leaf_router_0_0: C 10.0.0.0/24; B 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.8 (eth1)\\n    - leaf_router_0_1: C 10.0.1.0/24; B 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6 (eth0)\\n  - Spines and super-spine have BGP routes to both /24s via the expected neighbors.\\n- Interpretation: EBGP adjacencies and route propagation across the Clos tiers are normal. No control-plane anomalies detected.\\n\\nData Plane and Host-Level Findings\\n- pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24) is correctly configured:\\n  - IP: 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1\\n  - Reachability: pc_0_0 can ping its gateway 10.0.0.1 successfully.\\n  - Reachability across fabric to the remote leaf’s gateway works: pc_0_0 can ping 10.0.1.1 with 0% loss (~2.2 ms).\\n- pc_0_1 is down:\\n  - Host network query errors: “container ... is not running” for ifconfig/ip/route on pc_0_1.\\n  - From leaf_router_0_1, ping to 10.0.1.2 returns “Destination Host Unreachable” from 10.0.1.1, which is consistent with ARP failing because the host is offline.\\n- Interpretation: Inter-tier forwarding is functioning. The default gateways on the leaves are reachable end-to-end, proving the fabric’s data plane is operating. The only end-to-end failure observed is traffic destined to 10.0.1.2, directly attributable to the host being down.\\n\\nAnomalies Detected\\n- Endpoint pc_0_1 is not running (container stopped), causing 10.0.1.2 to be unreachable. This is confirmed both by:\\n  - Management plane errors when querying pc_0_1 (“container ... is not running”).\\n  - Data plane ICMP from leaf_router_0_1 to 10.0.1.2 returning “Destination Host Unreachable.”\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Faulty device: pc_0_1 (host container).\\n- Fabric devices (leaves, spines, super-spine) show no faults in BGP or routing; leaf and spine data-plane reachability appears intact based on gateway ping tests and routing tables.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- The host pc_0_1 is offline (container not running), preventing ARP resolution and IP connectivity to 10.0.1.2. The network fabric is not at fault; the issue is at the endpoint., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='70dfa5a4-5750-4af6-86a7-711c5f9f1b2f'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
